-- U.S. Said to Reach Accord With 3 Publishers on eBooks
-- B y   J e f f   B l i s s   a n d   S a r a   F o r d e n
-- 2012-04-11T14:15:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-11/u-s-said-to-reach-accord-with-3-publishers-on-ebooks.html
CBS Corp. (CBS) ’s Simon & Schuster,
Lagardère SCA’s Hachette Book Group and  News Corp. (NWSA) ’s
HarperCollins have agreed to settle allegations that they
conspired with Apple Inc. to set prices of digital books,
two people familiar with the matter said.  The U.S. filed an antitrust lawsuit today in Manhattan
federal court against Apple, Hachette, HarperCollins, Macmillan,
Penguin and Simon & Schuster claiming collusion over eBook
pricing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
